FBIS3-56142 "drsov009_m_94001" FBIS-SOV-94-009 Document Type:Daily Report 13 Jan 1994 Tajikistan State of Emergency Extended for 6 Months LD1201133994 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1312 GMT 12 Jan 94 LD1201133994 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service Language: Russian Article Type:BFN [By TIA correspondent Negmat Ochilov for TASS] [Text] Dushanbe, 12 Jan -- The Supreme Council Presidium of the Republic of Tajikistan has extended its decree of 6 January 1993 "On the introduction of a state of emergency in Dushanbe, the town of Tursunzade and its rayon, Shakhrinavskiy, Gissarskiy, Leninskiy, and Varzobskiy rayons, as well as the town of Kofarnikhon and its rayon for six months, until 8 June 1994." This measure was taken in order to stabilize the situation, establish the rule of law, and ensure the security of citizens, on the basis of Article 108 of the Constitution of Tajikistan.
